{{also|yahoo|Yahoo!}}
==English==
{{wikipedia|Yahoo (Gulliver's Travels)}}
===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|en|/ˈjɑːhuː/}}
===Etymology 1===
Coined by {{w|Jonathan Swift}} in ''{{w|Gulliver's Travels}}''. According to the ''{{w|Century Dictionary}}'', "[a] made name, prob[ably] meant to suggest disgust".
====Noun====
{{en-noun}}
# {{lb|en|fiction}} One of a race of [[brute]]s, who look and act similar to men, [[inhabit]]ing the same land as the [[civilized]] [[Houyhnhnm]]s.
#* {{RQ:Swift Gulliver's Travels|part=IV|chapter=VIII|pages=271–272|pageref=271|passage=I therefore often begged his Favour to let me go among the Herds of '''''Yahoos''''' in the Neighbourhood, to which he always very graciouſly conſented, being perfectly convinced, that the Hatred I bore thoſe Brutes, would never ſuffer me to be corrupted by them; {{...}}}}
=====Derived terms=====
* {{l|en|yahoo}}
===Etymology 2===
From the company name {{m|en|Yahoo%21|Yahoo!}}; see more on origin there.
====Noun====
{{en-noun}}
# {{lb|en|informal}} An [[employee]] of the Internet company [[Yahoo!]].
#* '''1996''', ''Newsweek'' (volume 127)
#*: But having two beaming Chief '''Yahoos''' on the cover is an implied seal of approval.
#* {{quote-book|en|year=2002|author=Karen Angel|title=Inside Yahoo!: reinvention and the road ahead|passage=Instead of driving down the street to meetings, soon '''Yahoos''' need merely stroll the walkways that crisscrossed a bright green lawn.}}
#* {{quote-book|en|year=2004|author=Chris Turner|title=Planet Simpson: how a cartoon masterpiece defined a generation|passage=Some '''Yahoos''' got filthy rich, but many more lost it all.}}
